41) EC2 Instance store
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EC2 Instance store basically used for temp storage inside your virtual server, for important storage you can go with EBS or USD drive etc.

42) EC2 Instance volume types
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) General purpose SSD
1 gb to 16 TB
If need balanaced performance.
usecase ; every day application , small database in dev/test env.

2) Provisioned IOPS SSD
4 gb to 16 TB
high performance
usecase : critical databaase,high performance applications.

3) Throughout optimized SSD. (High throughout)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
size 500 GB to 16 TB
use case - big data, data ware house , log processing 

4) COLD SSD (Infrequest access)
500 GB - 16 TB

5) Managetic (on budget) 
1 GB to 1 TB


43) EFS 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EFS Stands for elastic file system.
EFS is scalable and managed file storage services in AWS.
Managed storage service means user don't need to worry about the hardware and sotware of complexity to store the data
EFS is mutliregion network file.
EFS is great way to share the data into different zones.

44) EBS Vs EFS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EBS stands for elastic block storage volume whereas EFS stands for elastic file system.
EBS get attched at a time one instance expect multi-attched feature.
For migration we need to take the spanshot and restore it to the another AZ.

The main difference between EBS and EFS is EBS is used to persist the data , not for reflectons whereas 
EFS is used to to replicate data across all the Azones.
But primary focus of EFS is provide scalable and shared file storage within a single region.
where as S3 bucket provide data replicate and storage across all the avaibablity zones.


