    A. Spot Instances
    B. Savings Plans
    C. Dedicated Hosts
    D. On-Demand Instances

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Amith Bhanudas Aug 9, 12:20
Correct Answer - B. Savings Plans

https://aws.amazon.com/savingsplans/

Amith Bhanudas Aug 9, 12:20
Amazon EC2 Savings Plans enable you to reduce your compute costs by committing to a consistent amount of compute usage for a 1-year or 3-year term. This results in savings of up to 72% over On-Demand Instance costs. Any usage up to the commitment is charged at the discounted Savings Plan rate (for example, $10 an hour). Any usage beyond the commitment is charged at regular On-Demand Instance rates.

Manishkumar Nema Aug 9, 12:20
what if volumes spikes ? how does it gets adjusted ?

Avinish Agarwal Aug 9, 12:22
Why not use dedicated hosts? it also provides 70% cost saving?

Amith Bhanudas Aug 9, 12:26
Dedicated hosts have a specific use case, eg BYOL. This doesn't translate to cost savings if there is no such use cases. In fact, it can be more expensive.

Amazon EC2 Dedicated Hosts allow you to use your eligible software licenses from vendors such as Microsoft and Oracle on Amazon EC2, so that you get the flexibility and cost effectiveness of using your own licenses, but with the resiliency, simplicity and elasticity of AWS. An Amazon EC2 Dedicated Host is a physical server fully dedicated for your use, so you can help address corporate compliance requirements.

https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/dedicated-hosts/

